  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis — jobsquare\n\n**Baseline: zero tests exist.** No `tests/` directory, no pytest/respx/pytest-asyncio in `requirements.txt`, and no test step in `.github/workflows/scrape.yaml`. This is a full from-scratch gap analysis across all 8 modules (~2,000 LOC, dominated by `fetchers.py` at 1,024 lines / 20 ATS parsers).\n\n**Suggested test setup** (not yet present):\n```\n# requirements-dev.txt\npytest>=8.0\npytest-asyncio>=0.24\nrespx>=0.21          # mock httpx transport\nfreezegun>=1.5        # freeze datetime.now() for posted_at/cutoff tests\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. `models.py` — `parse_posted_at`, `Job`\n\nPure functions, zero deps, highest ROI for a first test file.\n\n**Gaps:**\n- ms-vs-seconds epoch boundary (`1_000_000_000_000` threshold) untested\n- negative/garbage/whitespace-only strings\n- ISO with trailing `Z`, ISO with no tz, ISO with existing offset\n- `Job.content_hash` only hashes `title|location|url|department` — **`employment_type`, `posted_at`, `salary_range` changes are silently invisible to dedup's \"changed\" detection.** Worth a test that documents this (likely intentional, but currently unverified behavior)\n- `to_row()` drops `raw`, injects `key`/`content_hash`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"value,expected_year\", [\n    (\"1643241332430\", 2022),       # Lever ms-epoch\n    (\"1643241332\", 2022),          # seconds-epoch\n    (\"999999999999\", 2001),        # just under the ms threshold\n    (\"1000000000000\", 2001),       # just at the ms threshold -> treated as ms\n    (\"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\", 2024),\n    (\"2024-01-15T10:00:00+00:00\", 2024),\n    (\"2024-01-15T10:00:00\", 2024), # naive -> assumed UTC\n])\ndef test_parse_posted_at_valid(value, expected_year):\n    dt = parse_posted_at(value)\n    assert dt is not None and dt.year == expected_year and dt.tzinfo is not None\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"value\", [\"\", None, \"   \", \"Posted 3 Days Ago\", \"not-a-date\"])\ndef test_parse_posted_at_unparseable_returns_none(value):\n    assert parse_posted_at(value) is None\n\ndef test_job_key_stable_across_field_edits():\n    j1 = Job(source=\"lever\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"A\", url=\"u1\")\n    j2 = Job(source=\"lever\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"B\", url=\"u2\")\n    assert j1.key == j2.key\n\ndef test_content_hash_changes_on_title_but_not_employment_type():\n    base = Job(source=\"lever\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"A\", url=\"u\")\n    same_type_changed = Job(source=\"lever\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                             title=\"A\", url=\"u\", employment_type=\"Contract\")\n    assert base.content_hash == same_type_changed.content_hash  # documents current blind spot\n    diff_title = Job(source=\"lever\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"B\", url=\"u\")\n    assert base.content_hash != diff_title.content_hash\n\ndef test_to_row_excludes_raw_and_includes_derived_fields():\n    j = Job(source=\"lever\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"A\", url=\"u\", raw={\"x\": 1})\n    row = j.to_row()\n    assert \"raw\" not in row\n    assert row[\"key\"] == j.key and row[\"content_hash\"] == j.content_hash\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. `filters.py` — `match`, `filter_jobs`\n\n**Gaps:**\n- exclude takes priority over include (both can match)\n- word-boundary regex semantics (`\"eng\"` must NOT match inside `\"Engineering\"`)\n- case-insensitivity of include/exclude/locations\n- cutoff boundary (`dt == cutoff` is kept, only `dt < cutoff` drops)\n- unparseable `posted_at` always survives a cutoff, regardless of `max_age_days`\n- empty/absent `rules` dict short-circuits to \"keep everything\"\n\n```python\n# tests/test_filters.py\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nimport pytest\nfrom models import Job\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\n\ndef _job(**kw):\n    defaults = dict(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Software Engineer\",\n                     url=\"u\", location=\"Remote\", department=\"Eng\")\n    return Job(**{**defaults, **kw})\n\ndef test_exclude_wins_over_include():\n    j = _job(title=\"Senior Software Engineer, Staffing\")\n    assert match(j, include=[\"Engineer\"], exclude=[\"Staffing\"]) is False\n\ndef test_word_boundary_does_not_match_substring():\n    j = _job(department=\"Engineering\")\n    assert match(j, include=[\"eng\"]) is False   # \"eng\" alone shouldn't hit \"Engineering\"\n\ndef test_include_case_insensitive():\n    j = _job(title=\"software engineer\")\n    assert match(j, include=[\"ENGINEER\"]) is True\n\ndef test_locations_substring_case_insensitive():\n    j = _job(location=\"San Francisco, CA\")\n    assert match(j, locations=[\"san francisco\"]) is True\n    assert match(j, locations=[\"Berlin\"]) is False\n\ndef test_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_posted_at():\n    j = _job(posted_at=\"Posted 3 Days Ago\")  # Workday prose, unparseable\n    cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=1)\n    assert match(j, cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\ndef test_cutoff_boundary_equal_is_kept():\n    now = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n    j = _job(posted_at=now.isoformat())\n    assert match(j, cutoff=now) is True   # only strictly-older is dropped\n\ndef test_cutoff_drops_older():\n    old = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=10)\n    j = _job(posted_at=old.isoformat())\n    cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=1)\n    assert match(j, cutoff=cutoff) is False\n\ndef test_filter_jobs_empty_rules_keeps_all():\n    jobs = [_job(external_id=str(i)) for i in range(3)]\n    assert filter_jobs(jobs, {}) == jobs\n\ndef test_filter_jobs_max_age_days_builds_cutoff():\n    fresh = _job(external_id=\"1\", posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())\n    stale = _job(external_id=\"2\", posted_at=(\n        datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)).isoformat())\n    out = filter_jobs([fresh, stale], {\"max_age_days\": 7})\n    assert out == [fresh]\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. `store.py` — `Store` (SQLite dedup)\n\n**Gaps:**\n- schema migration on a pre-existing DB missing `salary_range`\n- `diff()`: new/changed/unchanged branches, `last_seen` bump on unchanged\n- `next_seq` atomic increment (and its `BEGIN IMMEDIATE` concurrency guarantee)\n- `added_since` strict `>` boundary and ordering\n- `get_meta`/`set_meta` upsert\n- context-manager close\n\n```python\n# tests/test_store.py\nimport sqlite3\nimport pytest\nfrom store import Store\nfrom models import Job\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"test.db\") as s:\n        yield s\n\ndef _job(ext_id=\"1\", title=\"A\"):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=ext_id,\n               title=title, url=\"https://x\", location=\"Remote\")\n\ndef test_diff_new_job_inserted_and_returned(store):\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n    assert len(new) == 1 and changed == []\n    assert store.count() == 1\n\ndef test_diff_unchanged_job_only_bumps_last_seen(store):\n    store.diff([_job()])\n    row1 = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT last_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job()])  # identical content\n    assert new == [] and changed == []\n    row2 = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT last_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()\n    assert row2[\"last_seen\"] >= row1[\"last_seen\"]\n\ndef test_diff_changed_job_updates_and_returns_in_changed(store):\n    store.diff([_job(title=\"Old Title\")])\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job(title=\"New Title\")])\n    assert new == [] and len(changed) == 1\n    row = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT title FROM jobs\").fetchone()\n    assert row[\"title\"] == \"New Title\"\n\ndef test_migration_adds_salary_range_to_legacy_db(tmp_path):\n    path = tmp_path / \"legacy.db\"\n    conn = sqlite3.connect(path)\n    conn.executescript(\"\"\"\n        CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT, company TEXT,\n          external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT, department TEXT,\n          employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT, content_hash TEXT,\n          first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT);\n        CREATE TABLE meta (k TEXT PRIMARY KEY, v TEXT);\n    \"\"\")\n    conn.commit(); conn.close()\n    with Store(path) as s:\n        cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n        assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n\ndef test_get_set_meta_roundtrip_and_upsert(store):\n    assert store.get_meta(\"k\") is None\n    store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v1\")\n    store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v2\")  # upsert path\n    assert store.get_meta(\"k\") == \"v2\"\n\ndef test_next_seq_increments(store):\n    assert store.next_seq(\"report_seq\") == 1\n    assert store.next_seq(\"report_seq\") == 2\n\ndef test_added_since_strict_boundary_and_ordering(store):\n    store.diff([_job(ext_id=\"1\")])\n    ts = store.get_meta.__self__.conn.execute(\n        \"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()[\"first_seen\"]\n    assert store.added_since(ts) == []          # equal ts excluded (strict >)\n    assert len(store.added_since(\"2000-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")) == 1\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. `pipeline.py` — `load_config`, `run`\n\n**Gaps:**\n- config defaulting (missing `sources`/`filters`/`db`/`concurrency`)\n- `dry_run=True` never touches `Store`/`dispatch`\n- full happy-path orchestration with everything mocked\n- `run_sync` actually drives the coroutine\n\n```python\n# tests/test_pipeline.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import AsyncMock, patch\nimport pipeline\n\ndef test_load_config_fills_defaults(tmp_path):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"min.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n    cfg = pipeline.load_config(cfg_path)\n    assert cfg[\"filters\"] == {} and cfg[\"db\"] == \"jobs.db\" and cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 8\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_dry_run_skips_store_and_dispatch(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(pipeline, \"fetch_all\", AsyncMock(return_value=[]))\n    with patch.object(pipeline, \"Store\") as MockStore, \\\n         patch.object(pipeline, \"dispatch\") as mock_dispatch:\n        result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path, dry_run=True)\n        MockStore.assert_not_called()\n        mock_dispatch.assert_not_called()\n        assert result == {\"matched\": 0, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_run_calls_diff_and_dispatch_with_filtered_jobs(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n    # ... mock fetch_all -> filter_jobs -> Store.diff -> dispatch call order\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. `notify.py` — 5 notifiers + `dispatch`\n\n**Highest-value gap: `dispatch()`'s failure isolation is completely unverified.** If `notify_slack` throws, do `notify_webhook`/`notify_email`/`notify_sms` still run? The `try/except` around each call in `dispatch` suggests yes, but nothing proves it.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_notify.py\nimport pytest\nimport respx\nimport httpx\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nfrom models import Job\nimport notify\n\ndef _job(**kw):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\",\n               url=\"https://x\", **kw)\n\ndef test_notify_console_no_fresh_listings(capsys):\n    notify.notify_console([], [])\n    assert \"No fresh listings\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\ndef test_notify_slack_noop_without_env(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n    with respx.mock:\n        notify.notify_slack([_job()], [])  # would raise if it tried to POST\n        assert not respx.calls\n\ndef test_notify_slack_noop_when_no_jobs(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack.com/x\")\n    with respx.mock:\n        notify.notify_slack([], [])\n        assert not respx.calls\n\n@respx.mock\ndef test_notify_slack_posts_payload(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack.com/x\")\n    route = respx.post(\"https://hooks.slack.com/x\").mock(\n        return_value=httpx.Response(200))\n    notify.notify_slack([_job(salary_range=\"$100k-$150k\")], [])\n    assert route.called\n    body = route.calls[0].request.content\n    assert b\"100k\" in body\n\ndef test_sms_body_truncates_at_limit():\n    jobs = [_job(external_id=str(i), title=f\"Role {i}\") for i in range(10)]\n    body = notify._sms_body(jobs, [], limit=8)\n    assert \"+2 more\" in body\n    assert body.count(\"\\n- \") == 8\n\ndef test_notify_sms_noop_unless_all_four_env_vars_set(monkeypatch):\n    for var in (\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", \"TWILIO_FROM\", \"TWILIO_TO\"):\n        monkeypatch.delenv(var, raising=False)\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"sid\")  # only 1 of 4\n    with respx.mock:\n        notify.notify_sms([_job()], [])\n        assert not respx.calls\n\ndef test_dispatch_isolates_notifier_failures(monkeypatch, capsys):\n    with patch.object(notify, \"notify_slack\", side_effect=RuntimeError(\"boom\")), \\\n         patch.object(notify, \"notify_webhook\") as mock_webhook:\n        notify.dispatch([_job()], [])\n        mock_webhook.assert_called_once()   # still ran despite slack raising\n        assert \"notifier notify_slack failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. `fetchers.py` — parsers (unit, pure) and `fetch_*` (integration, mocked HTTP)\n\nThis file is the largest risk surface: 20 `parse_*`/`_*` normalizers and 13 `fetch_*` functions, all currently untested, several with subtle defensive/fallback logic that's exactly the kind of thing that silently breaks (per your own memory notes on Meta's doc_id rotation and the Google careers fetch trap).\n\n### 6a. Parser unit tests (representative — same pattern applies to all ~20)\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_parsers.py\nfrom fetchers import (parse_greenhouse, parse_lever, _lever_salary, parse_ashby,\n                       _extract_ds1, parse_google, _ds1_posted_at, _apple_hydration,\n                       _apple_posted_at, parse_apple, _bd_location, parse_amazon,\n                       _amazon_posted_at, parse_microsoft, parse_netflix)\n\ndef test_parse_greenhouse_joins_multiple_departments():\n    data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"Eng\", \"absolute_url\": \"u\",\n                       \"location\": {\"name\": \"Remote\"},\n                       \"departments\": [{\"name\": \"A\"}, {\"name\": \"B\"}],\n                       \"updated_at\": \"2024-01-01\"}]}\n    out = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", data)\n    assert out[0].department == \"A, B\"\n\ndef test_lever_salary_prefers_range_over_description():\n    j = {\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 100000, \"max\": 150000, \"currency\": \"USD\"},\n         \"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"ignored\"}\n    assert _lever_salary(j) == \"USD 100,000–150,000\"\n\ndef test_lever_salary_falls_back_to_description_when_no_range():\n    assert _lever_salary({\"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"Competitive\"}) == \"Competitive\"\n\ndef test_parse_ashby_skips_unlisted_jobs():\n    data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"isListed\": False, \"title\": \"Hidden\"},\n                      {\"id\": \"2\", \"isListed\": True, \"title\": \"Visible\"}]}\n    out = parse_ashby(\"acme\", data)\n    assert len(out) == 1 and out[0].title == \"Visible\"\n\ndef test_extract_ds1_handles_missing_sidechannel_fallback():\n    html = 'AF_initDataCallback({key: \\'ds:1\\', data:[[[\"1\",\"Title\"]]]});'\n    assert _extract_ds1(html) == [[\"1\", \"Title\"]]\n\ndef test_extract_ds1_returns_empty_on_malformed_json():\n    html = \"key: 'ds:1', data:[not valid json], sideChannel:{}\"\n    assert _extract_ds1(html) == []\n\ndef test_ds1_posted_at_prefers_create_over_update_time():\n    job = [None]*15\n    job[12] = [1700000000]  # create\n    job[13] = [1800000000]  # update\n    result = _ds1_posted_at(job)\n    assert \"2023\" in result  # create-time year, not update-time\n\ndef test_ds1_posted_at_defensive_on_short_array():\n    assert _ds1_posted_at([1, 2]) == \"\"\n\ndef test_apple_hydration_none_when_marker_absent():\n    assert _apple_hydration(\"<html>no hydration here</html>\") is None\n\ndef test_apple_posted_at_trims_nanosecond_precision():\n    result = _apple_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:03.812668311Z\")\n    assert result == \"2024-01-15T10:00:03.812668+00:00\"\n\ndef test_apple_posted_at_empty_on_missing_value():\n    assert _apple_posted_at(\"\") == \"\"\n\ndef test_bd_location_walks_parent_chain():\n    city = {\"en_name\": \"Beijing\", \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"China\", \"parent\": None}}\n    assert _bd_location(city) == \"Beijing, China\"\n\ndef test_bd_location_none_returns_empty_string():\n    assert _bd_location(None) == \"\"\n\ndef test_amazon_posted_at_parses_us_format():\n    assert _amazon_posted_at(\"June 26, 2026\") == \"2026-06-26T00:00:00+00:00\"\n\ndef test_amazon_posted_at_unknown_month_returns_empty():\n    assert _amazon_posted_at(\"Frobnary 26, 2026\") == \"\"\n\ndef test_amazon_posted_at_malformed_returns_empty():\n    assert _amazon_posted_at(\"not a date\") == \"\"\n\ndef test_parse_amazon_falls_back_to_id_icims():\n    out = parse_amazon(\"amazon\", [{\"id_icims\": \"123\", \"title\": \"Eng\", \"job_path\": \"/p\"}])\n    assert out[0].external_id == \"123\"\n\ndef test_parse_microsoft_missing_posted_ts_is_empty_string():\n    out = parse_microsoft(\"microsoft\", [{\"id\": \"1\", \"name\": \"Eng\"}])\n    assert out[0].posted_at == \"\"\n\ndef test_parse_netflix_falls_back_to_single_location_field():\n    out = parse_netflix(\"netflix\", [{\"id\": \"1\", \"name\": \"Eng\", \"location\": \"SF,CA,US\"}])\n    assert out[0].location == \"SF, CA, US\"\n```\n\n### 6b. `_request` retry/error-handling (currently completely untested)\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_request.py\nimport httpx, pytest, respx\nfrom fetchers import _request\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_request_retries_on_503_then_succeeds():\n    route = respx.get(\"https://x/api\").mock(side_effect=[\n        httpx.Response(503), httpx.Response(200, json={\"ok\": True})])\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        r = await _request(client, \"https://x/api\", retries=3)\n    assert r.status_code == 200 and route.call_count == 2\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_request_exhausts_retries_raises_runtime_error():\n    respx.get(\"https://x/api\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(500))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"failed to fetch\"):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x/api\", retries=2)\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_request_non_retryable_4xx_raises_immediately_no_retry():\n    route = respx.get(\"https://x/api\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(404))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x/api\", retries=4)\n    assert route.call_count == 1  # not retried\n```\n\n### 6c. `fetch_*` pagination/dedup integration tests (representative)\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_fetch_microsoft.py\nimport httpx, pytest, respx\nfrom fetchers import fetch_microsoft\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_fetch_microsoft_stops_on_empty_page():\n    respx.get(\"https://apply.careers.microsoft.com/api/pcsx/search\").mock(side_effect=[\n        httpx.Response(200, json={\"data\": {\"positions\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"name\": \"A\"}]}}),\n        httpx.Response(200, json={\"data\": {\"positions\": []}}),\n    ])\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        jobs = await fetch_microsoft(client, {\"max_pages\": 5})\n    assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_fetch_microsoft_dedups_across_pages():\n    respx.get(\"https://apply.careers.microsoft.com/api/pcsx/search\").mock(side_effect=[\n        httpx.Response(200, json={\"data\": {\"positions\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"name\": \"A\"}]}}),\n        httpx.Response(200, json={\"data\": {\"positions\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"name\": \"A\"}]}}),  # dup\n    ])\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        jobs = await fetch_microsoft(client, {\"max_pages\": 5})\n    assert len(jobs) == 1  # second page's repeat stops pagination via \"fresh empty\"\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_fetch_microsoft_respects_max_pages_cap():\n    respx.get(\"https://apply.careers.microsoft.com/api/pcsx/search\").mock(\n        return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\n            \"data\": {\"positions\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"name\": \"A\"}]}}))  # always \"fresh\" (diff calls, same id each time actually dedups...)\n    # use per-call unique ids to force the cap to be the actual stop condition\n```\n*(Same skeleton shape applies to `fetch_netflix`, `fetch_amazon`, `fetch_apple`, `fetch_eightfold`, `fetch_optiver`, `fetch_twosigma`, `fetch_google`, `fetch_bytedance`, `fetch_workday` — each has its own pagination param name and stop condition worth asserting individually.)*\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_fetch_meta.py\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_fetch_meta_strips_for_loop_prefix_and_parses():\n    respx.get(\"https://www.metacareers.com/jobs\").mock(\n        return_value=httpx.Response(200, text='[\"LSD\",[],{\"token\":\"abc\"}] \"__spin_r\":5'))\n    respx.post(\"https://www.metacareers.com/graphql\").mock(\n        return_value=httpx.Response(200, text='for (;;);{\"data\":{'\n            '\"job_search_with_featured_jobs_v2\":{\"all_jobs\":[{\"id\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Eng\"}]}}}'))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        jobs = await fetch_meta(client, {})\n    assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_fetch_meta_raises_runtime_error_on_graphql_errors():\n    # simulates the rotated-doc_id failure mode from your memory notes\n    respx.get(\"https://www.metacareers.com/jobs\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(200, text=\"\"))\n    respx.post(\"https://www.metacareers.com/graphql\").mock(\n        return_value=httpx.Response(200, text='{\"errors\":[{\"message\":\"bad doc_id\"}]}'))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"bad doc_id\"):\n            await fetch_meta(client, {})\n```\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_dispatch.py\nimport httpx, pytest, respx\nfrom fetchers import fetch_source, fetch_all\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_source_unknown_ats_raises_value_error():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n            await fetch_source(client, {\"ats\": \"nonexistent\"})\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\n@respx.mock\nasync def test_fetch_all_isolates_one_source_failure(capsys):\n    respx.get(\"https://boards-api.greenhouse.io/v1/boards/good/jobs\").mock(\n        return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": []}))\n    sources = [{\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"good\"}, {\"ats\": \"unknown-ats\"}]\n    jobs = await fetch_all(sources)\n    assert jobs == []  # both empty, but the run didn't crash\n    assert \"failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_all_does_not_close_externally_provided_client():\n    client = httpx.AsyncClient()\n    await fetch_all([], client=client)\n    assert not client.is_closed\n    await client.aclose()\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. `agent.py` — CLI + PDF normalization (currently zero coverage)\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `cmd_db_new`: first-run windowing, `--posted-days`/`--dated-only` interaction, group-boundary-safe truncation\n- `cmd_db_mark`: `--now`, valid/invalid explicit watermark, neither-passed error\n- `_normalize_ats`: each Unicode substitution rule, and — critically — that it **skips** `<style>`/`<script>` blocks\n- `_chrome_bin` discovery order (env var → PATH → hardcoded app paths → `sys.exit`)\n- `cmd_pdf_render`: missing input file, `%PDF` magic-byte failure detection, temp-file cleanup on both success and failure paths\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent.py\nimport pytest\nfrom agent import cmd_db_mark, cmd_db_new, _normalize_ats\nfrom store import Store\n\ndef test_db_mark_now_sets_current_timestamp(tmp_path, capsys):\n    db = tmp_path / \"j.db\"\n    cmd_db_mark([\"--now\", \"-c\", str(_write_min_config(tmp_path, db))])\n    with Store(db) as s:\n        assert s.get_meta(\"last_scan\") is not None\n\ndef test_db_mark_invalid_watermark_exits_2(tmp_path):\n    cfg = _write_min_config(tmp_path, tmp_path / \"j.db\")\n    assert cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-timestamp\", \"-c\", str(cfg)]) == 2\n\ndef test_db_mark_no_args_exits_2(tmp_path):\n    cfg = _write_min_config(tmp_path, tmp_path / \"j.db\")\n    assert cmd_db_mark([\"-c\", str(cfg)]) == 2\n\ndef test_normalize_ats_replaces_smart_quotes_and_em_dash():\n    html, counts = _normalize_ats(\"<p>He said \\u201chi\\u201d \\u2014 once.</p>\")\n    assert '\"hi\"' in html and \"- once\" in html\n    assert counts[\"smart-double-quote\"] == 2 and counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1\n\ndef test_normalize_ats_skips_style_and_script_blocks():\n    html = \"<style>content: '\\u2014';</style><p>real \\u2014 dash</p>\"\n    out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n    assert \"\\u2014\" in out.split(\"</style>\")[0]   # untouched inside <style>\n    assert \"real - dash\" in out                    # replaced in body\n    assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1                   # only the body occurrence counted\n\ndef test_db_new_first_run_uses_since_days_window(tmp_path):\n    # seed Store with jobs at varying first_seen, call cmd_db_new with no prior marker,\n    # assert only rows within FIRST_RUN_DAYS window (default 7) appear and\n    # printed JSON has first_run=True\n    ...\n\ndef test_db_new_group_boundary_truncation_never_splits_a_first_seen_group(tmp_path):\n    # seed 3 jobs sharing one first_seen timestamp, set --limit 2\n    # assert either all 3 are included (group kept whole) or none are (truncated before group)\n    ...\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Integration-test gaps (cross-module, currently entirely absent)\n\n| Gap | Why it matters |\n|---|---|\n| `pipeline.run()` end-to-end with a real `Store` (tmp_path db) and mocked `fetch_all` | Only integration test proving fetch→filter→diff→notify→count actually wires together |\n| `agent.py db-new` → `db-mark` round trip against a real `Store` | Verifies the marker never causes a job to be skipped or double-reported across two scans |\n| `dispatch()` with 2+ real env-configured notifiers, one raising | Per your `jobsquare-parallel-worker-collisions` memory, notifier/pipeline failures interacting with shared state is a known risk area |\n| CLI `--dry-run` leaves `jobs.db` row count unchanged | Guards the one safety property `--dry-run` promises |\n| `fetch_all` against `sources.yaml`'s actual source list, with all HTTP mocked via `respx` | Catches config/fetcher signature mismatches (e.g. a source entry missing a required key like `host`/`tenant` for Workday) without hitting the network |\n\n---\n\n## Priority order if implementing incrementally\n\n1. **`models.py` + `filters.py`** — pure, no mocking needed, cheap wins, and directly gate correctness of every downstream job.\n2. **`store.py`** — protects the dedup/migration logic that the whole scheduled pipeline depends on.\n3. **`notify.py` `dispatch()` isolation** — a regression here silently drops all remaining notifications.\n4. **`fetchers.py` parsers** — pure functions, no HTTP mocking, and this is where source-specific fragility actually lives (per your memory notes on Meta/Google/ByteDance quirks).\n5. **`fetchers.py` fetch_* pagination + `agent.py`** — needs `respx`; lower frequency of change but highest blast radius when a platform changes its API shape.\n\nWant me to scaffold these as actual