        "title": "6. `fetchers.py` — parsers (unit, pure) and `fetch_*` (integration, mocked HTTP)",
        "content": "\nThis file is the largest risk surface: 20 `parse_*`/`_*` normalizers and 13 `fetch_*` functions, all currently untested, several with subtle defensive/fallback logic that's exactly the kind of thing that silently breaks (per your own memory notes on Meta's doc_id rotation and the Google careers fetch trap).\n\n",
        "level": 2
